 bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=metaskie>Metaskie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 10:25:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> Are the DE guards in OT on the same DreadGuard Inner/Outer as the Neriak guards? If not, would a halfelven rogue be KOS?  If i am KOS from the zone in, would there be enough time to activate my DE Illusion (never been to OT before, but plan on going once i hit 32)?  One final question, again, if im KOS to there faction, are there any quests that i can raise this faction with? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urimidal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rimidal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 10:28:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> they're all on Venril Sathir faction <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uflaamwing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flaamwing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 10:40:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> The outpost is all on Venril Sathir faction, neriak guards are on something else - forget what.<br><br>You can kill berzerker's and each one will drop a whip, if you turn in 4 whips to the guard captain you will get a junk shield and some faction.<br><br>Killing in HS, Kaesora, or some places in Karnors will also lower this faction.<br><br>I havent found anything to kill which raises this faction yet though, anyone else?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukrodahdirtnappah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krodah Dirtnappah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 10:49:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> Kunark dragons raise VS faction <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uazzallinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzallinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 10:57:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> Gorenaire, Severilious, faydedar, Talendor, and Trakanon all give positive Venril Sathir faction, I trully believe killing mobs in skyfire should give positive VS faction but verant didn't want that to happen apparently, anyone been to veeshans peak? whats the faction hits like there? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udachunker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dachunker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 11:46:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> In a vain effort to fix my VS faction and get the workers sledge mallet ( port to OT proc ) I tried to rack up as many positive VS hits as i could.  Started out with bottomed out VS faction, cleared VP 3 times, got every dragon hit, gore twice, telendor 2 times, sev once, and a few trak hits. Drumroll..... I had enough faction with VS that I lost it all in about 15 minutes of dog killing in KC.  I figure if you killed every Kunark dargon every time they spawned, you might have positive VS faction in roughly decade if you started with bottomed out faction.  <br><br>Dachunker<br>&lt;Lotus Cult&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uillia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Illia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 1:15:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> VS faction...<br><br>If you never drop below dubious, you can do the whip quest in OT to raise faction.  (Rogues may be able to sneak/hide while KOS).<br><br>If you're KOS though, you're hooped.  The ONLY verified mobs which give +VS faction are the Kunark Dragons.<br><br>Talendor, Severlious, Gorrenaire, Faydedar, Silverwing, Xygoz, Phara, Nexona, Druush, Hoshkar.<br><br>Escorpa of the Ring is probably the easiest of the bunch,  he/she is in west wastes, as the Ring of Scale's rep there.<br>(I have not personally verified this faction hit, it could be any number of hits instead)<br><br>Basically you need to kill mobs which are on the Ring of Scale faction  (Ringofscale as first hit).<br><br>Figure though if you can get the 18 people together to kill those dragons on a regular basis, you probably don't care about VS anymore.<br><br>My suggestion is to say &quot;screw it&quot;.  Howling stones is a really good dungeon,  and well worth the trade off.  Note that it takes about 5 mins to go from Amiable to KOS (to VS, you're always kos in HS) while killing in HS.  <br><br>--Illia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaspomwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aspomwell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 7:06:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure sneaking will work (you don't get faction if yer hidden, right?).  Captain Rottgrime is who you turn the braids into and he's always facing his men, or walking back and forth.  You may be able to sneak up behind him but you'll be facing 4 or 5 undead marines.<br><br>I love using my hammer too much to lose my VS faction. :/<br><br>Lykos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 7:47:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> Heyas-<br><br>Even KOS folks can do the braid quest if they are sufficiently motivated.  Takes a LONG time tho, and help from friendly casting class toons.<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 9:03:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9675.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT Faction Question</span><hr size=1> trak doesn't give VS faction, all other kunark dragons do though. takes a lot of dragons to get even dubious...i was max scowl and killed at least 15 dragons, still scowling.<br><br>you can also get the hammer by charming the quest giver (you need puppet strings from fear golems, old CT drop), pets con amiable and you can get hammer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecre